Attention Deficit Disorder (ADD):

• Attention Deficit Disorder or ADD is a neurochemical disorder
• The patient is not able to perform tasks which require a focussed effort

Symptoms to look for:

• Disorganized behaviour
• Incapable of paying attention to details
• Incapable of following directions 
• Randomly jumping from one task to another
• Lack of concentration

Causes:

• Imbalance of certain chemicals in the brain
• Certain nerve groups which are out of their position in the brain

